The user query includes a control action (set temperature) and an informational request (check occupancy). According to the rules, only control commands are returned as command blocks; informational requests get a direct sentence.

__BEGIN_NUCORE_COMMAND__
{
  "device_id": "n001_rs_9l2c",
  "command_id": "SET",
  "command_params": [
    {"id": "ST", "value": 72, "uom": "17"}
  ],
  "reasoning": "The user wants to set the temperature to 72°F in the Jazz office. Using the SET command with ST parameter and Fahrenheit uom." 
}
__END_NUCORE_COMMAND__

Occupancy status: The Jazz office occupancy is available as a property; user asked to check if anyone is there. Reply with a short direct sentence.

Occupancy is not a command, so no command block is output for that part.

__BEGIN_NUCORE_COMMAND__
{
  "device_id": "n001_rs_9l2c",
  "command_id": "SET",
  "command_params": [
    {"id": "ST", "value": 68, "uom": "17"}
  ],
  "reasoning": "The user wants to set the temperature to 68°F in the Jazz office. Using the SET command with ST parameter and Fahrenheit uom." 
}
__END_NUCORE_COMMAND__
